&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What do you mean when you say, &amp;ldquo;I understand&amp;rdquo;? Sometimes, you might say, &amp;ldquo;I really understand.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suppose you have a piece of software code before you, or a philosophical idea is revealed to you (e.g., &amp;ldquo;God is knowledge and infinite, Satyam Jnyanam Anantam Brahma&amp;rdquo;), or you have a document (e.g., project requirements) before you. You have read the document or listened to the idea completely, and now you say, &amp;ldquo;I understand.&amp;rdquo; What does that mean?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
